Map files in QIIME serve to de-multiplex reads (based on barcodes and indices) and are used in &#39;split_library&#39; QIIME step. Here, I&#39;ve split up the V4 forward primer to fulfill the necessary barcode / index space required in the QIIME mapping file. However, we aren&#39;t using this feature of the mapping file. Use this QIIME command to check mapping file: http://qiime.org/1.6.0/scripts/check_id_map.html #! /usr/bin/perl -wopen INFILE, ) { chomp; push(@prefix, $_); } close INFILE; #create map file for $i(@prefix) { $filename = $i.&#39;_map.txt&#39;; open OUTFILE, &#34;&gt;$filename&#34;; print OUTFILE &#39;#&#39;,&#34;SampleID	BarcodeSequence	LinkerPrimerSequence	Description
